# Public API the Electron/browser app calls (gateway OR main-server).
#
# /rag/* from the browser: prefer main-server (port 8081 by default) — CORS is configured there.
# Raw ragServer (:8082) is for server-to-server; the browser needs CORS on ragServer if you use :8082.
#
# Defaults are driven by src/config/serverProfile.ts (ACTIVE_SERVER_PROFILE). Uncomment to override:

# Option A — API gateway (preferred: frontend → gateway → main-server)
#VITE_API_BASE=http://192.168.0.10:8080

# When the gateway does NOT proxy /rag/*, point the SPA at main-server (not ragServer :8082 unless rag has CORS):
#VITE_RAG_BASE=http://192.168.0.34:8081

# Option B — direct to main-server only if you intentionally bypass the gateway (replace host as needed)
#VITE_API_BASE=http://192.168.0.34:8081

# HWPX: in dev the app POSTs to http://<same-host-as-the-page>:8789/convert — run `npm run hwpx-server` on that machine.
# Override to use Spring on main-server instead of Python: http://127.0.0.1:8081/api/hwpx
#VITE_HWPX_CONVERTER_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8081/api/hwpx
